docker pull ubuntu - to pull ubuntu image from hub/registry
docker images - to check images
df-h - to check the size of image
docker run ubuntu - to create container (will be in exit state)
docker run -it --name madhu ubuntu - to give name to container and will be in running state
docker run -itd --name madhu ubuntu - it will give name to the container, if we come out of the container will still be in up state
docker attach madhu - to go into container
NOW CREATE SOME FILES AND INSTALL PACKAGES
docker commit madhu image1 - all the files created in madhu (container) are now converted into image
